<section id="1_section">
    <h2 class="cp-subtitle">Overview and key figures</h2>

    <p>According to OECD DAC figures, in 2014, Belgium delivered USD 2.4 billion in net ODA, which represented 0.46% of
        gross national income (GNI) and an increase of 5.8% from 2013. This represents a slight reversal of the downward
        trend in ODA, which decreased both in terms of volume and as a percentage of GNI from a peak of 0.64% in 2010.
        Belgium is the 9th largest Development Assistance Committee (DAC) donor in terms of ODA as a percentage of GNI
        and the 14th donor in terms of volume. The outlook for growth in Belgium’s ODA is negative, however the
        government is committed to the target of 0.7% ODA/GNI, which is enshrined in law. </p>

