<section id="8_section">
    <h2 class="cp-subtitle">Channels of cooperation/approach</h2>

    <p>Having begun with a project focus, the partnership later evolved to focus on field programmes as well as support to national policies. In line with its full core policy, Belgium is now concentrating its support on FAO’s regular budget, while being a major contributor to the FAO Multi-Partner Programme Support Mechanism – the main channel for non-emergency Belgian funding today – as well as the FAO Special Fund for Emergency Activities and other facilities.</p>

    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>Multi-partner programme support mechanism (FMM)
            </li>
         <li>Belgian Fund for Food Security (BFFS)
        </li>
        <li>FAO Special Fund for Emergency Activities-SFERA (humanitarian interventions)</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
        Delegated cooperation negotiated directly at country level with the Belgian embassies. This mechanism was applied in 2014 in the Democratic Republic of Congo and Niger.
        Decentralized cooperation with the regions of Flanders and Wallonia.
    </p>

</section>

